main event: A farmer spotted a circular, metallic object hovering and maneuvering in the sky near Gwinner, North Dakota in 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be about 50 feet in diameter and emitted a bright light.
The object hovered for several minutes before quickly accelerating and disappearing from view.
The witness, Mr. Gwinner, was able to take several photographs of the object before it disappeared.
No conclusive explanation for the sighting was determined by the investigation.
The case has been classified as 'Unidentified' in the Project Blue Book archives.
